Privacy Policy for Mizo Dictionary
Last updated: [Date, e.g., December 22, 2025]
This Privacy Policy describes how Zo Entertainment ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and discloses information when you use our mobile application, Mizo Dictionary (the "App").
By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
1. Information Collection and Use
a. Personal Information The App does not require you to create an account or provide personally identifiable information (such as your name, address, or phone number) to use its primary features.
b. Usage Data & Device Information We use third-party services that may collect information used to identify your device. This data may include your device's Internet Protocol ("IP") address, device name, operating system version, the configuration of the app when utilizing the service, the time and date of your use of the service, and other statistics.
c. Search & Translation Data
•
Dictionary Search: Your search history and favorites are stored locally on your device using a database. We do not transmit this data to our servers.
•
AI Translation: The App uses Google Gemini (Generative AI) for translation features. When you use the translation feature, the text you input is sent to Google's servers to be processed and returned. This data is used solely for the purpose of generating the translation.
2. Third-Party Service Providers
We use the following third-party services to facilitate our App and provide its features:
•
AdMob (Google Mobile Ads): We use AdMob to display banner, interstitial, and native advertisements. AdMob may use your device's Advertising ID to show personalized ads.
•
Google Generative AI (Gemini): Used for providing Mizo-English translations.
•
Google Play Services: Used for app functionality and distribution.
Links to the privacy policies of third-party service providers used by the App:
•
Google Play Services
•
AdMob
•
Google Generative AI
3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
The App uses "cookies" or similar technologies provided by our third-party advertising partners (AdMob) to collect information and improve their services. You have the option to either accept or refuse these cookies and know when a cookie is being sent to your device. If you choose to refuse our cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of this Service (e.g., rewarded ads).
4. Text-to-Speech (TTS)
The App utilizes the Android Text-to-Speech (TTS) engine installed on your device to pronounce English words. This interaction happens locally on your device and does not transmit data to us.
5. Security
We value your trust in providing us your information. However, remember that no method of transmission over the internet, or method of electronic storage is 100% secure and reliable, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
6. Children’s Privacy
These Services do not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. In the case we discover that a child under 13 has provided us with personal information, we immediately delete this from our servers. If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so that we will be able to do the necessary actions.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or suggestions about our Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us at:
